      <hedline>
        <hl1>Queensberry Rules</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>J H Poivan letter corrects Miranda Seymour's June 18 review of Douglas Murray's book Bosie</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Miranda Seymour quotes the inscription (''For Oscar Wilde -- posing as a sodomite'') on the Marquess of Queensberry's card that precipitated the events leading to the trial of Oscar Wilde. Queensberry, an authority on boxing but apparently not on spelling, actually wrote, ''To Oscar Wilde posing Somdomite,'' according to Richard Ellmann's biography.</p>
        <p>J. H. Poivan  Pennington, N.J.</p>
      </block>
